comment._content: www.defense.gov/photos/newsphoto.aspx?newsphotoid=525 U.S. Navy A-6E Intruder receives signal to launch from catapult three of USS Enterprise (CVN 65), on Dec. 19, 1996, marking the last Intruder squadron to fly from the deck of an aircraft carrier. The Intruder, from VA- 75 'Sunday Punchers', Naval Air Station Oceana, Va., sports AG tail code and paint scheme representing Carrier Air Wing 7, the squadron's first air wing over 30 years before. DoD photo by Petty Officer 2nd Class Alan Warner, U.S. Navy. 961219-N-2101W-001_screen.jpg
